node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marvel Facts on September 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Daredevil's Charlie Cox responds to Spider Man: No Way Home trailer rumour. "Ican can promise you, those are not my forearms.'.

node.text:
The speculation began to swirl when a shot of a man's forearms in what looked to be an interrogation scene intrigued viewers of the latest No Way Home trailer, who quickly dissected the similarities between Matt Murdock's limbs and those of a stranger. Now, as Charlie Cox promotes his latest project Kin, the actor has put to bed theories.

node.text:
Venom: Let There Be Carnage Rating Confirmed!

The motion picture association revealed the official age rating for Venom 2 and fans hoping for a viscerally violent film may be disappointed! According to FilmRatings.com, Venom is rated PG-13. The reasoning behind it is because the film contains "intense sequences of violence's and action, some strong language, disturbing material and suggestive references"

Is anyone disappointed by this?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marvel Facts on August 25, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'MARVEL STUDIOS SPIDER-MAN No Way HomE The long-awaited first trailer for Marvel Studios and Sony Pictures 'Spider- Man: No Way Home' has come and gone, with no trace of the rumoured Tobey Maguire from the Sam Raimi trilogy in sight. However, one of the film's stars may have just turned that rumour into a fact @MarvelousFacts'.

node.text:
While speaking with The Illuminerdi, J.B. Smoove (who plays Peter Parker’s deadpan teacher Mr. Dell) was asked which Spider-Man he was most excited to see Tom Holland’s web-slinger team up with: Andrew Garfield’s or Tobey Maguire’s. “Whooo! Toby Maguire, of course, man” Smoove said in an almost suspiciously nonchalant manner. 

Hmm ... What do you think?🤨
